<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="../../w/index-title=Template_talk_English_official_language_clickable_map&action=edit&section=9.php.html" title="Edit section: Link">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Link">Link</span></h2>
<p>Is there a reason there is no link to <a href="Scottish_English" title="Scottish English">Scottish English</a> while the template links to Mid-Ulster English? The political status of both areas are practically identical, and British English is the written variety in both while being the spoken variety in neither. <a href="User_Deacon_of_Pndapetzim" title="User:Deacon of Pndapetzim">Deacon of Pndapetzim</a> (<small><a href="User_talk_Deacon_of_Pndapetzim" title="User talk:Deacon of Pndapetzim">Talk</a></small>) 11:27, 18 December 2008 (UTC)</p>
